headline: Wealthy Families Lean Into Private Credit, Infrastructure Investments, BlackRock Finds
summary: Private credit and infrastructure markets are attracting more interest from investors—and, amid heightened geopolitical uncertainty, family offices are no exception.  A survey of 175 single-family offices found that more than a third (39%) plan to increase their exposure to private credit in the coming year, either by adding to existing positions or initiating new ones—the most of any asset class.  Sentiment was similarly strong regarding infrastructure: 32% of family offices said they were planning to start or expand positions, while just 2% expect to pull back.
